de.esoco.storage

Class StorageRelationTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.esoco.storage.StorageRelationTypes

  • @Annotations.RelationTypeNamespace(value="de.esoco.storage")
public class StorageRelationTypes
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains relation types for storage implementations. Besides generic types it also defines some types for certain storage implementations, i.e. mainly for relations with metadata for the SQL/JDBC implementation.

    • Field Detail

      • STORING

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Boolean> STORING
        A flag that is mainly used internally by storage implementations to indicate that a object is currently being stored. This may also be used by storage-related application code to detect whether an object is made persistent, although there may be storage implementations that do not support this flag.

      • PERSISTENT

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Boolean> PERSISTENT
        A flag to designate objects that already exist in a storage. It will be set by storage implementations on objects that have been stored in or read from the underlying storage. The flag is final because a persistent object is considered to be associated with the corresponding object for it's full lifetime. Therefore, to store an object as new in the same or a different storage a copy of the original object must be created.

      • STORAGE_NAME

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.String> STORAGE_NAME
        Contains the generic storage name of an element. This name will be used to represent an object in a storage if the storage implementation supports such naming and if no property that is more specific to the respective storage implementation is set on the object (like JdbcRelationTypes.SQL_NAME).

      • STORAGE_DATATYPE

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Class<?>> STORAGE_DATATYPE
        This property can be set on some storage elements to define the datatype to be used for storage operations. For example, it must exist on attribute definitions returned by StorageMapping implementations if the method Storage.initObjectStorage(StorageMapping) is used to initialize some storage implementations (e.g. a JDBC-based storage).

      • STORAGE_LENGTH

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Integer> STORAGE_LENGTH
        Defines the (maximum) length of a storage field. It depends on the storage implementation and field datatype mapping if and how this attribute is evaluated. If it is not the default value (2048) will be used.

      • STORAGE_DEFINITION

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<StorageDefinition> STORAGE_DEFINITION
        Contains a reference to the storage definition of a storage.

      • STORAGE_MAPPING

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<StorageMapping<?,?,?>> STORAGE_MAPPING
        Contains the storage mapping for the object where it has been set on.

      • QUERY_DEPTH

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Integer> QUERY_DEPTH
        Defines the maximum depth which a query should descend in the graph of an object. If this relation is not set the complete hierarchy of an object will be fetched. A value of zero means that no children should be fetched at all. This relation can be set on many storage-related objects as shown below. The priority is from top to bottom, i.e. the topmost relations override the lower (more generic) ones:
        1. on a query result
        2. on a query
        3. on a query predicate
        4. on the criteria predicate of a query predicate
        5. on a storage instance as the default for all of it's queries
        6. on a storage definition as the default for all storages of that definition

        Attention: some storage implementations may only support setting the query depth on a subset of these levels. Please check the documentation of the used implementation for such limitations.

        The default value is Integer.MAX_VALUE to indicate an unlimited query depth. Implementations that cannot handle this value should check for the existence of the relation instead.

      • QUERY_OFFSET

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Integer> QUERY_OFFSET
        Can be set on a storage query to define the position of the first record to be returned by the query. Has a default value of 0 (zero).

      • QUERY_LIMIT

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Integer> QUERY_LIMIT
        Can be set on a storage query to limit the number of records that will be returned by the query. The default value is zero for no limit.

      • STORAGE_QUERY_SIZE

        public static final org.obrel.core.RelationType<java.lang.Integer> STORAGE_QUERY_SIZE
        The size of a storage query. This relation can be used to store the size of a storage query. It is not filled automatically by the storage query.
